    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Imperatores Caesares <expan><abbr>d<am>d</am></abbr><ex>omini</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>n<am>n</am></abbr><ex>ostri</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/>Valentinianus <supplied reason="lost">e</supplied>t Valens fratres <lb n="3"/>concordissimi victores maximi <lb n="4"/>ac triumphatores semperque Augusti <lb n="5"/>muros cum turribus horum cas<lb break="no" n="6"/>trorum a rudimentis fundamento<lb break="no" n="7"/>rum consurgere imperarunt dispo<lb break="no" n="8"/>nente Equitio <expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>iro</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>c</abbr><ex>larissimo</ex></expan> comite <expan><abbr>mag</abbr><ex>istro</ex></expan> equitum <lb n="9"/>peditumque cur<supplied reason="lost">a</supplied>nte Augustiano <lb n="10"/><del rend="erasure"><expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>iro</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>c</abbr><ex>larissimo</ex></expan> comite <expan><abbr>ord</abbr><ex>inis</ex></expan></del> pr<supplied reason="lost">i</supplied>mi et duce <expan><abbr>Val</abbr><ex>eriae</ex></expan> limitis <lb n="11"/>numini clementi<expan><ex>a</ex><abbr>eq</abbr></expan><supplied reason="lost">u</supplied>e eorum dicatissimis
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Tafel mittig vertikal in zwei aneinanderpassende Teile zerbrochen. Wohl aus dem Kastell von Esztergom-Hideglelőskereszt verschleppt. Z. 10: nachträgliche Tilgung des einem dux Valeriae limitis nicht zustehenden, irrtümlich eingehauenen Rangtitels eines vir clarissimus comes ordinis primi. Datierung: Equitius war magister utriusque militiae ab 365, ab 24. August 367 war Gratian, der hier nicht genannt wird, Augustus. (B): CIL 03, 10596; ILS: Z. 10: Abweichungen in Lesung/Ergänzung.</p>
            </div>
